Dear Adam,

It was nice to meet you Friday the week before last, I hope you had some ti=
me to think about your Banking relationship going forward, I wanted to shar=
e with you an idea for a product that we are doing here in EdR and to ask y=
ou if you saw that kind of products from other Banks as well.

I have attached the presentation of the idea and also the USD KFD, I think =
that in a portfolio today you should also have some of your assets invested=
 in this kind of products as we discussed.

Would like to hear a feedback, and see what are you interested in.

Kind regards,

Moshe



[X]

[X]

INVESTMENTS FLASH
Private Banking


DEFENSIVE EXPOSURE TO OIL COMPANIES



LOWER PRICES AND HIGHER VOLATILITY

Since the start of the downturn in late 2014, investors have been very scep=
tic about the capital discipline of big oil integrated companies. Quite the=
 contrary, thanks to strong operational performances and low capital expend=
itures, these actors are now able to give shareholders returns in the form =
of cash dividends or share buybacks.

The significant reduction of cash flow break-even (far from present spot pr=
ice) is probably the key highlight of the updated groups' strategy. It stan=
ds now below US$50/barrel by 2021, driven by a combination of higher-margin=
 production and improved performance across the mid and downstream division=
s.

Thus, we propose you an interesting investment opportunity to benefit from =
the current levels of volatility on 2 recommended stocks to generate an att=
ractive yield while offering a conditional capital protection at maturity.


KEY ELEMENTS
>       Maturity : 18 months
>       Currency: USD, EUR and CHF (quanto - no FX Risk)
>       Possible quarterly coupon payment and automatic early redemption
>       100% capital protection against a negative performance up to -25% i=
n stock prices (strike at 75% of initial level)
>       If the negative performance is superior to -25%, receive the worst-=
performing share at the strike level






Worst performing stock among :
Currency
Conditional coupons

Total (FP FP) and Royal Dutch Shell (RDSA NA)
USD
1.85% per quarter (i.e. 7.40% p.a.)


EUR
1.00% per quarter (i.e. 4.00% p.a.)


CHF
0.90% per quarter (i.e. 3.60% p.a.)



The details for the products' launch are :
         >          Expected trade date on Wednesday November 28th, 2018
         >          Investment by multiples of USD/EUR/CHF 1,000, minimum o=
f 100K
      >          Issuer - to be determined from the list of approved counte=
rparts (A- minimum S&P rating)
         >          Indicative lending value of 65%

















